column7: Material finery shall never win me over, dearest, but: It helps! Here, while we're feeling generous, I'll send you something, too.
An offering imbued with your affections, little godling? I'll positively drink it up first chance I get; and I want you to have something of mine.
To your dignified countenance, Lady Athena, I'd direct only the kindest and sincerest compliments! Whatever else?
Who dares threaten my little godling?
Just leave it to me, dearest!
I like the sound of that.
I won't forget this, not anytime soon!
Hold on, I have something for you!
There's something I wish you to have.
Well that did not turn out.
You don't want to make me angrier.
I've not the time for this.
I knew your heart was true!
Your heart shall never carry you astray.
I'll pierce them through the heart!
Oh it shall be my pleasure!
I knew your heart was true!
Your heart shall never carry you astray.
I'll pierce them through the heart!
Oh it shall be my pleasure!
You break my heart, I break your body, little godling.
You ought to worship me, rather than anger me.
Don't you refuse my good graces like that again.
